  "name": "Retail Express Hardware Utility Error",
  "body": "<h1 data-id=\"retail-express-hardware-utility-error\">Retail Express Hardware Utility Error</h1>\n<p><strong><span>Retail Express Hardware Utility Error</span></strong><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>?The Application Binding Data Format is Invalid?</span><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>Hardware Utility ? Failing During Process</span><span> </span></p>\n<p><em><span>Overview</span></em><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>Error message is similar to below, it just doesn?t have the line </span><em><span>?The application is missing required files?.</span></em><span> </span></p>\n<p><img alt=\"rtaImage - 2023-07-09T231029.057.png\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphjZEAQ.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></p>\n<p><span>This issue stems from a previous </span><em><span>?temporary fix?</span></em><span> that was implemented in the system, involving the creation of a secondary profile </span><em><span>(with a clean installation of the software) </span></em><span>for Retail Express Hardware Utility Install failures. If the software is removed from the old profile, instead of the REX-created profile </span><em><span>(generally called REX),</span></em><span> it will result in an endless loop where the Hardware Utility can?t be deleted, nor can it be installed.</span><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>The resulting error page will occur when the REX Hardware Utility Software attempts to install and will present an error page that has minimal text, with only 2 options: </span><strong><em><span>?Details?</span></em></strong><span> and </span><strong><em><span>?OK?</span></em></strong><span>. Selecting </span><strong><em><span>?Details? </span></em></strong><span>will open a text document through Notepad, which shows an error message approximately halfway down the page with the error message code reading:</span><span> </span></p>\n<p><img alt=\"rtaImage - 2023-07-09T231033.929.png\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000ppgomEAA.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><span> </span></p>\n<p><em><span>Resolution</span></em><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>There were 2 main actions taken to resolve this issue. The first was to </span><strong><em><span>Update the Registry,</span></em></strong><span> and the second was to </span><strong><em><span>Delete the Apps folder.</span></em></strong><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>Updating Registry</span><span> </span></p>\n<ol><li><span>Open the Registry Editor </span><em><span>(Regedit)</span></em><span> </span></li><li><span>Navigate to the following Registry file on the machine:</span><span> </span><br/><em><span>&lt;HKEY_CURRENT_USER\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Uninstall\\e95250b3a5d94c01&gt;</span></em><span> </span></li><li><span>Delete the Entry from the Registry </span><strong><em><span>AFTER ATTEMPTING TO UNINSTALL FROM WINDOWS.</span></em></strong><span> </span></li><li><span>Close the Registry Editor.</span><span> </span></li></ol><p><span>Deleting the Apps Folder</span><span> </span></p>\n<ol><li><span>Open File Explorer in Windows</span><span> </span></li><li><span>Navigate to:</span><span> </span><br/><em><span>&lt;C:\\Users\\$USERPROFILE$\\AppData\\Local\\Apps&gt;</span></em><span> </span></li><li><span>Delete folder ?2.0? </span><em><span>(shown below)</span></em><span> </span><br/><img alt=\"rtaImage - 2023-07-09T231039.393.png\" src=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=300,width=300/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg 300w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=600,width=600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg 600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=800,width=800/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg 800w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1200,width=1200/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg 1200w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=1600,width=1600/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg 1600w, https://us.v-cdn.net/cdn-cgi/image/quality=80,format=auto,fit=scale-down,height=2000,width=2000/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg 2000w, https://us.v-cdn.net/6038474/uploads/attachments/migrated/image.05T5g00000pphbwEAA.jpg\" sizes=\"100vw\" class=\"embedImage-img importedEmbed-img\"></img></li></ol><p><em><span>Manually Install Tyro Terminal Adapter (Optional)</span></em><span> </span></p>\n<p><span>After performing these two fixes, you may still need to manually install the Tyro Terminal Adapter before running the Hardware Utility </span><em><span>(depending on if they use Tyro)</span></em><span>. If so, you should:</span><span> </span></p>\n<ol><li><span>Navigate to:</span><span> </span><br/><span>&lt;</span><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http://galaxy.maropost.com/home/leaving?allowTrusted=1&amp;target=https%3A%2F%2Ftyro.com%2Ftta\"><span><a href=\"http://galaxy.maropost.com/home/leaving?allowTrusted=1&amp;target=https%3A%2F%2Ftyro.com%2Ftta\">https://tyro.com/tta</a></span></a><span>&gt;</span><span> </span></li></ol><p><span>This will start the download of the Tyro Terminal Adapter</span><span> </span></p>\n<ol><li><span>Run the application and follow the prompts to install the software. </span><span> </span></li><li><span>Run the Retail Express Hardware Utility</span><span> </span></li></ol><p><span>This should resolve the issues with your Retail Express Hardware Utility. </span><span> </span></p>",
